{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778264810,"nonce":"z1ubVkvzY9ZCYzEXMlMAcPxTYCc=","title":"Add compositional hidden-state smoothness penalty (||ḣ_t||²) to feedbax loss menu; retrain baseline as A/B test","message":"## Motivation\n\nTrajectory-level replicate variability in delayed-reach trained controllers (within-condition pairwise RMSE 0.39–0.45 m/s, comparable to across-condition RMSE) currently invalidates inter-condition comparisons. Literature investigation identifies missing trajectory-shape regularisation as the leading driver. The closest peer paper, **Shahbazi, Codol, Michaels \u0026 Gribble 2025** ([bioRxiv](https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2025.03.26.645562)), uses an \\`||ḣ_t||²\\` hidden-state smoothness penalty at weight 1e-3 plus a jerk penalty at 1e5 — terms that directly constrain how the latent state and output evolve through the preparation and movement epochs. rlrmp has neither.\n\n## Implementation\n\n**Compositional, not baked in.** The smoothness term must be a reusable component in feedbax's loss menu, wireable into any loss configuration alongside existing terms (position-error, control-effort, hold-cost, activity-L2, etc.). Shape:\n\n- New \\`LossWeights\\` field, e.g. \\`nn_hidden_derivative\\`.\n- New term in feedbax's loss-construction module computing \\`mean(||h_t - h_{t-1}||²)\\` (or continuous-time equivalent), scaled by the configured weight.\n- Wireable into the loss dict via standard rlrmp config patterns (\\`config/modules/training/*.yml\\`), not hard-coded in the training script.\n\n**Initial weight: 1e-3** (matching Shahbazi 2025 Eq. 1).\n\n## Test plan\n\nA/B retrain of the baseline model (no adversary, standard backprop, 5 replicates) — once with the smoothness term, once without. Measure within-condition pairwise RMSE on post-go forward velocity profiles. If the term collapses replicate variance to a usable level, adopt as default for all training runs going forward.\n\n## Escalation (NOT yet filed as separate issues — documented for record)\n\nIf the smoothness term alone is insufficient:\n1. Add jerk penalty on output trajectory (weight 1e5).\n2. Bump existing activity L2 (\\`nn_hidden\\`, \\`nn_output\\`) from 1e-5 to 1e-3.\n3. Vanilla-RNN ablation (replace GRU with RNNCell).\n4. Low-rank recurrent constraint.\n\n## Cross-references\n\n- Phase umbrella \\`f695729\\` — this is a **blocker**: inter-condition comparisons cannot reliably be made until variability is suppressed.\n- Synthesis: \\`results/flavor_a_vs_b/synthesis.md\\` §7.\n- Diagnostic + literature: \\`/tmp/flavor_ab_review/findings/empirical_diagnosis.md\\`, \\`/tmp/flavor_ab_review/findings/replicate_variability_lit.md\\`.\n- Plot showing the variance: \\`/tmp/flavor_ab_review/plots/forward_velocity_0p5m.html\\` (per-trial-aligned).\n\n## Implementation notes\n\nFeedbax-side change requires a feature branch from feedbax \\`develop\\` (feedbax's protected branch is \\`develop\\`, not \\`main\\`). The rlrmp-side wiring + baseline retrain config follows on a sibling rlrmp feature branch from \\`main\\`.","files":null}]}